column6: Event Description
The real question is, what're THOSE? Find a friendly tourguide in the courtyard for an East Campus dorm tour! Leaves approximately every half hour.
Do people live here? Find a friendly tourguide in the courtyard for an East Campus dorm tour! Leaves approximately every half hour
Warning: Wild student-humans in their natural habitat - Do not feed! Find a friendly tourguide in the courtyard for an East Campus dorm tour! Leaves approximately every half hour.
"EAST THE DORM" Find a friendly tourguide in the courtyard for an East Campus dorm tour! Leaves approximately every half hour.
East Campus? I thought you said WEAST Campus! Find a friendly tourguide in the courtyard for an East Campus dorm tour! Leaves approximately every half hour.
Ahoy mateys! Come join us to sail the seven seas, here for a short time right at East Campus! Come enjoy a burger, some construction, and a nice chitchat.
Power tools! Ladders! Safety! No experience required, burgers provided
Burgers and friends ALL DAY
Burgers and friends ALL DAY
Burgers and friends ALL DAY
Exercise your freedom of expression by dying your hair ALL OF THE COLORS.
Hair is temporary, bleach is permanent, instagam likes are forever.
What better way to appreciate the spirit of individualism and self-reliance than to get your hair dyed in ALL OF THE COLORS because you can and why not.
If you're worried about what your parents will think, natural colors such as leaf green, sky blue, and grape purple also available.
We've been coloring hair so long that our hands have literally turned into rainbows. Please advise.
Asking questions in exchange for some sweet treats from Trader Joes!
Where‚Äôs ‚Äúhere‚Äù <thinking emoji>?
Come join us in not-being-here.
Time, much like our existence during this block of time, is but an illusion

Ahoy mateys! East Side Party, where the songs don't stop coming. Ride our student-made attractions, get space trained, and wrestle in substances never before wrestled in. And as you dance and get to experience our pirate den, you too will taste the sweet nectar of freedom. Shiver me timbers!
We shall fight to the death and WIN!!!!! (and by death I mean we shall soak them completely)

Come hang out and make some blackout poetry! We'll take some sharpies 
and redact random book pages until poetry emerges. Fruits provided, for 
some much-needed REX-time vitamin C! Fruity poetry welcomed.
An informative panel about what it's like to be queer at MIT, including resources and firsthand accounts from queer studets in East Campus (this event not open to parents)
Come tattoo yourself or get tattooed with inkbox or henna! Such ink is temporary, but the rad is 5ever.

Ahoy mateys! Got scurvy? Looking for some nice cold drink after your hard work building for rush? Well we've got you! Drive? Bike? Walk? Skate? Sail? or come up with some other clever way of navigating yourself to the outside window of the 1st west parallel where we will be serving smoothies, orange juice and fruit! Come to the kitchen to help out or enjoy the vibes and the views of the rush coaster outside :)

Come for: sugar, carbs, friendship, enough food to induce a coma, and napping locations if need be <3

Do not come for: waffles, vegetables, dignity in what you put in your body (unless that means CRUELTY-FREE, BABY!), or kite-flying
Join us on the East Campus courtyard for an evening of poetry and a safe space for queer expression. Bring your favorite poems or just come along to listen. Snacks will be provided!

Grill various fruit, I don't care if it makes sense, if it's a fruit, it's gonna be aflame eg: pineapple, peaches, tomato (genuinely good), bananas (weirdly good), oranges (genuinely bad), grapes, lychee, apples, berries, mango, basically anything I can get my hands on.
Cook and/or eat breakfast in a kitchen and hang out with residents.
Cook and/or eat breakfast in a kitchen and hang out with residents.
Come build & hang out in a fun blanket fort on EC 3rd East (Tetazoo)! Will start right after folks come home from the water war
Paint on yourself or an EC resident, because painting on your skin doesn't just have to be on your face!
Paint the 4E fridges blue! Come help paint the fridges for a beautiful kitchen for EC's last year before renovations! Fun designs or just solid, we are painting them blue

if you were on tumblr in middle school, you may be entitled to financial compensation. you're probably not going to get it though so come watch good omens and our flag means death instead. Comes with snacks!
Queer? Asian? Both? Neither? Whatever, come have some bubble tea (with RAINBOW TAPIOCA! oooh, ahhh) and chat with us :))

Come sit around and work on various crafts/projects with EC residents, types of projects/crafts can include, but are not limited to: clothes alteration, painting, crocheting/knitting, clay creations, origami, construction paper & felt work, and more!!
Cookies and a Look Into MacG's Entry System
A Showing of The VelociPastor, Pool Volleyball, and Dinosaur Chicken Nuggets

column1: MacGregor Could Use A Little Color
column6: Color the sidewalks of MacG with chalk, then stick around for trivia and karaoke!
We will press your very own custom artisanal panEnE! As you eat, join us playing on the Switch or help decorate our lounge.
Come play board games with E entry, while enjoying brownees and freshly hand-made coffee! (or tea, or hot chocolate)
Come grab a balloon animal or a balloon sword and eat popcorn with Gentry residents!
Come sing tunes and eat some delicious ramen with H and G entry, also known as HEX!
Show up to bake some yummy yummy cookies, and enjoy them while playing games in the lounge!
Play some smash then pass it off while you meet the members of A entry
Chill at the top of the high rise with a entry and get to know our entry and residents. Did we mention there‚Äôs chipotle?

RC CAR COMPETITION! 
HOMEMADE RACETRACK!

column3: F Entry Lounge (Up the stone staircase in the courtyard)
column6: Come compete in our festival of improv goodness, or come simply to enjoy the spectacle of your friends presenting nonsensical powepoints prepared by Fentry. No previous experience needed, showing up for food and entertainment also encouraged.

column3: F Entry Lounge (Up the stone staircase in the courtyard)
column6: A variety of homecooked food made by the residents of F Entry.
Escape the heat and cool off with ice pops and mocktails while enjoying the B entry view
Get ready for the day with a pancake and waffle bar, including bacon and OJ
Enjoy snacks while playing board games and meeting some B entry residents
Enjoy dinner and a show with J entry as you work together to solve a murder mystery
Watch memes, eat cereal, and hang out with the residents of J entry
Come enjoy our party on McCormick's East Penthouse ! Bring a date! or 2, or 3! (no but like please come, we've spent insane amounts of money on this )

Channel your inner POKER savant and join McCormick for a night filled with gambling and mocktails (we only gamble with Lady Luck here, no money)!!! Bring your friends and dominate them in blackjack, mahjong, and MOREEE

Bounce house obstacle course! Cotton candy, popcorn, snow cones!  Games and PRIZES GALORE! We're having a giant carnival bash, and we're giving away SO MUCH FOOD AND PRIZES! All genders invited, and bring your friends!
FOOD!FREE FOOD! All hungry pre-frosh welcome, first come first serve!

Have THE ICONIC TOSCANINI's ICE CREAM on McCormick's front lawn! Why settle for regular ice cream when you can have BOSTON'S BEST? For multiple years, Tosci's has been voted by Bostonians to be the BEST and come see why! Also just chill and spill tea with us;)
Have a chill breakfast before rushing off to REX events!

What's better than free art supplies? Painting the best view in MIT with those supplies, of course! Paint the Boston skyline from the penthouse, and make a personalized door sign as a bonus! Art supplies and snacks provided :)

column1: Who's smarter than an MIT professor?
column6: Y'all got into MIT, so clearly there's something going on in your brains. But are you smarter than the folks who ADMITTED YOU?  Or feeling super gutsy? Step into the ring with a professor!
Craving the sweet tase of victory? Face off against teams and come help us demolish decorate and eat some cakes and cupcakes!
Ready to make some friends to spend a fun REX week with? We are here to help!
Chill, relax, put on a face mask! Enjoy a spa night with us before heading off to your first week of classes!
GAMES you say? WASTE THE NIGHT AWAY WITH US IN McCormick's Game room :) Any game you could ask for (INCLUDING MARIO, SMASH, PING PONG, POOL, AND MORE! )
New tour every hour, on the hour! Get an insider tour of McCormick, including the Penthouse, Dance Studio, Craft Room, Country Kitchen, Gym, and more!
New tour every hour, on the hour! Get an insider tour of McCormick, including the Penthouse, Dance Studio, Craft Room, Country Kitchen, Gym, and more!
Need new accessories for the start of the school year? Come learn how to make jewelry with the members of Juniper!
Welcome the new Juniper house with chicken, waffles, and Beyonc√©'s Homecoming
Come through and listen to some classics in RnB, Hip Hop, Rap, Soul, and much more!

Whether you want to come face off against our assortment of King K. Rool mains in Smash Ultimate, question literally everything and everyone while playing Secret Hitler and Codenames, or take part in a team challenge in Hanabi or The Mind, Desmond's got the game for you.  Come for snacks freshly delivered from H-Mart and good vibes guaranteed.

Cloud Bread? Cheesecake Cookie Bars? Chocolate Chip Banana Bread? We've got you covered. Armed with our arsenal of bowls, flour, and whisks, you'll be able to work with a team of friends or Desmondites to make all of your confectionary dreams come true! In the end, we'll all have one big feast and share our creations‚Äîboth the instagram-worthy and the inevitable monstrosities ;)

Are you America's next superstar waiting to be discovered? Or perhaps you just like belting classics like Country Roads in the car? You've seen it at CPW, but get ready for Season 2 of Desmond's Got Talent! We invite you to take on the stage (or rather, the lounge karaoke machine) once again at our Late Night Karaoke session! Come cavort, caper, and consume Canes' crispy fried chicken while you sing!
It's midnight(ish), we got waffles, we got loads of whipped cream and other toppings. What more is there to say?
Bored? Come play BOARD games with German House! We have snacks galore, and German Housers who will crush you in Mario Kart.
Is REX getting to be too much and you'd rather KNOT for a while?  Come chill for a bit while we bake pretzels and watch game shows!
Spent too much time coding? You're an Olympiad kid? Come play games outside! We'll be playing volleyball and other sports, and eating plenty of post-game snacks.
A karaoke event like you've never experienced before. Join House 4's favorite weeknight tradition of singing and dancing your heart out in the kitchen!
Groovy music, juicy burgers, and a sunset by the river. Come hang out with House 4 for a chill vibe-y time :-)
Curious about your past, present, or future self? Or just want to chill and eat levain cookies? Come get your (tarot) cards or (astrology) chart read by your resident house 4 astrologers!
U read that right, you're invited to GLOW ALL OUT AT HOUSE 4!! We're talking glow sticks, LED lights, and music that won't disappoint. get ready to dance and party all night long!

column3: iHouse Kitchen (next to New House front desk)
column6: Come check out the iHouse kitchen and lounge with some hotpot! We'll have meat and vegetarian broths

column3: iHouse Kitchen (next to New House front desk)
column6: Too much exploration in these residences? Come to the iHouse kitchen, where there's an equal chance our TV will play the 5hr iCarly analysis, anime, or a documentary at any point in the day! Dining on our donuts while watching docus is (almost) a must!
Come meet La Casa and enjoy our bi-annual Carne Asada
Join La Casa for a night of board games and tacos. Secret Hitler, Exploding Kittens, and more! (No actual kittens were or will be harmed)
Ready to dance? Come bust some moves for a chance to win a TV!
Don't lock yourself out of your room, in style
Feeling like you want to make some friends and enemies in a competitive environment? Come play celebrity/fishbowl/salad toss!
Choose your own adventure banana bread baking - the only requirements are bananas and broadway tunes!
Exhausted from REX? Enjoy a sweet crepes and hot chocolate breakfast to energize you for the day!
Join French House in sampling cheeses and teas as we spill the proverbial tea on life at MIT!
Come meet DormCon, the group organizing all of REX! We can chat about how the week has been for you guys, shitpost about student government, and share some Trader Joes snacks :D
Tour around Next House, led by a current Next House resident. Learn more about Next House culture. Open to parents.
Tour around Next House, led by a current Next House resident. Learn more about Next House culture. Open to parents.
Come by if you would like to consume some Spicy Noodles! (Bringing your own container and utensils are Highly Encouraged!)

We're going to make something short, sweet, and berry delicious (STRAWBERRY SHORTCAKE). Don't be fooled by our childlike theme, this is serious business‚Äîat least, our baking is! Try your hand at this delicate dessert and whip up some cake and cream with Next Bake. We (just might) be watching Strawberry Shortcakes Berry Bitty Adventures in the background (no copyright infringement, and also 23% chance we do this), so there won't be a dull moment!

Some events include: - cornhole with actual corn: "the description is self explanatory" - saturday morning cursed cartoons: "not your typical saturday morning" - ? drawing competition: "not a drawing competition of an unknown subject, but a drawing competition of ?s" - 1000 piece custom puzzle: "Jeffery (adj.): having the quality of a Jeffer" (who's Jeffery? come and find out!) snaccs will be provided

Various amounts of cookies. Cookie variants may include: dough made that day; dough made the night before and chilled overnight, vegan/gluten/nut-free, chocolate chip.

Drink tea, do crafts, wear your favorite crazy (or not-so-crazy) hat, and discuss life, the universe, and everything with a bunch of friendly Nexties! If you don't have any hats, come use our miscellaneous art/craft supplies to make one! If you have too many hats... wear all of them?

column1: Crab Rave (just dance with the sims!)
column6: Come have some fun and show off your best dance moves with the Sims in a Just Dance marathon of epic proportions!

Have you ever wanted the chance to run around a group of strangers you just met and arbitrarily choose one to soak with a giant sponge? ME TOO! Come play duck duck sponge! It's like duck duck goose but literally better :)
Come make and eat dumplings! (Vegetarian and non-pork dumplings included)
Telegrams, velociraptors, and maybe even a dog. All locked with you in one room. Will you survive? Probably not, and the velociraptors deserve a snack anyway.

It's sick and twisted how cookie dough ice cream doesn't have enough cookie dough. Let's solve that by smashing some massive chunks of heavenly cookie dough into ice cream. Join us to make some extreme ice cream sundaes from big ol' cakes, cookies, pastries, and candies.

column1: Fancy Little Tea Party for Fancy Folks
column6: Are you a fancy lad looking for some refined company? Join us to sample an array of pastries and delightful little sandwiches while haughtily talking about sophisticated topics we know nothing about like "The economy!" *fake laughter*

column3: 2nd floor hammock lounge and hallways/lounge staircases on the way to 7th floor terrace, plus Celevator to return chairs to 2nd floor hammock lounge
column6: Roll around the erupting Mount Simmons in chairs. Move from lounge to lounge without touching the floor and boucing off the walls. Velociraptor repelent not provided.
pool table madness with this simmons classic
pool table madness with this simmons classic
pool table madness with this simmons classic
One giant, puzzlingly-shaped dorm. One giant, actual (jigsaw) puzzle. One entire day. If you want to help us put this puzzle together, feel free to stop by for as long or short as you want!
Come play with some giant stuff while eating some mini food! We'll have objects from giant teddy bears and a giant chess set, and some giant games as well!
eat bbq at the simmons grills! we've got burgers & dogs(hot), as well as veggie options!
eat homemade ice cream with the simmons house team!
Do you like doggos? Big floofers? Absolute units of cuddles? Well, come meet Kaito!

A meal of delicious, exquisite chicken nuggets will be provided for our amazing freshmen. Come join and get to eat with your new simmons pals.  Which dipping sauce is superior in your opinion??? Let's find out at late night nugs :)
There can only be one college meal to rise above the others, and we need you to decide. Vegetarian options available.

Wondering what it's like to be queer at MIT/Simmons? Come chat with some residents about their MIT experience to ask any questions you have and meet some extremely cool (gay) people. There will be rainbows galore, and I dare say it will be magical.

Amateur chefs + fancy cake recipe = ???
Grab some pizza, meet some Simms, or just relax after an action-packed day!
young, spongy, and ducky?
Come fold paper into fun shapes and talk to us!! Paper and instructions will be provided, or you can wow us with your own amazing creations ;)

column1: Pancake breakfast: a new batch of prefrosh
column6: Not so long ago, in a dorm kitchen not so far far away, there were many pancakes waiting to be eaten. Come meet some great people, chat about simmons and MIT, and eat some delicious (FREE) pancakes!

column1: Pancake breakfast: return of the syrup
column6: Though the first batch may have been eaten already, many pancakes still remain. Come hang out and get a delicious breakfast made of the 3 key nutritional food groups: Pancakes, toppings, and syrup!

column1: Pancake breakfast: the syrup strikes back
column6: We're you so busy soaking in all our other toppings that you forgot about the syrup? Syrup doesn't like to be forgotten.

column1: pancake breakfast: orange you sad it's over?
column6: Last, but certainly not least! Come help us finish off our pancakes and have a great time! (no promises that we will have oranges)
Come destress and pop bubbles. Who can resist??
Whether you have participated in MIT Mystery Hunt before or you think this is an event that somehow combines jigsaw puzzles and scavenger hunts, come chill and solve some puzzles with us! - 01101010

What happens when you take the scootahs from PE class and combine it with hockey? Do you get a sporting bout worthy of the Olympics? No! Far greater! Olympians wish they could play scootah hockey! Around 5% of applicants get into MIT and less than 1% of them will be crowned Scootah Hockey champions! Will it be you?
Prepare for the water war by painting shields for West Campus!

Explore what it means to be a Sim at Simfest, Simmons most Simmonsy event featuring mini events throughout the dorm. Come play mahjong, tape our dorm president to the wall, or decorate rubber ducks! Participate in sports like gatas, ping pong, and mario kart! Eat some cheese, gelatinized foods, or miracle berries! There are even more events to discover at this crash course of Simmons culture.
Put your gamer skills to the test to defeat Old Simms, New Simms, and everyone in between in Smash Ultimate!
Come take a tour of Main Street and visit H-MART! If you miss us leaving, meet us coming back to the Sponge with our spoils (ramen).

Hungry? I hope so. We've prepared a classic spaghetti dinner just for you, where you can make your own pasta dinner ahd choose sauces, meats, and veggies. Gluten free and vegan options available. [this time with enough pasta]
Need a break from some crazy REX activities? Come eat snacks and watch everyone's favorite Sponge in the sponge!

column1: The blocks are strong with us
column6: May the 4th be with you.. wait what it's not May any more? Join us to chill, chat and snack as we take on a build from the LEGO Star Wars collection!
come party atop the most porous dorm! we have music & mocktails. bad dancing is encouraged

Come fill some water balloons and buckets to prep for the ultimate battle.
You joust, but with wheely chairs and pool noodles.

Join us for a Maseeh traditional of Smash bracket tournament style! Prizes will be given to the winners.
Join us and celebrate the Olympics by competing with and against your fellow first years in various Olympic events & yard games.
Live like a Pinterest post with Maseeh sunrise painting, complete with locally sourced charcuterie boards of course!

WATER BALLOON FIGHTTT!! 'nuff said. Plus, if you get tired, you can also chill in our ac'd Conner 4 lounge and drink our free boba.

column1: C5 Snacks, Smash, and Mario Kart
column6: Want to show off your god gamer skillz? Just wanna hang out and play video games with some chill people and even better snacks? Do both with C5!

Remember field day? Compete in fun games with Burton Conner!! Including but not limited to: tug of war, forehead oreo challenge, dizzy bat, jell-o slurping race, 3-legged race, a bunch of other races, you get the idea...
Come relive the early 2000s and get tinsel put in your hair! Kombucha will be made as well as to drink!
come build pillow forts with C2!!! pj's optional. other activities include nail painting and stuffed animal show and tell ;D
imag1ne: an open dancefloor, your local b-oners, an absolute banger of a bop. What. Do. You. Do. Come learn how to drop it like a b-oner from our very own MIT dance biddies (no dance skills required)

have you ever had blue p1zza? neither have we. make your own (mostly) blue pizza. the more creative (or graphic), the better.
Because carving your own marble is unBritish (and won't win you the Apple Bake). Venus de Milo? More like Venus de Milocalfarmers'market.
grab some brunch & baked goods with burton third!

Are you ever overcome by the spontaneous urge to smash fruit? Eat fruit? Smash fruit and eat it? Eat fruit and smash it? Come satisfy these desires with Conner 3!
Do you like green eggs and ham? Come enjoy green breakfast with Conner 3 to find out!

Ever watched the Great British baking show? Like that, but instead of British it's Irish*. And instead of professional bakers it's college students. And instead of unobstructed vision it's blindfolded. On the brightside, no hand-eye coordination required!
*we aren't even fully Irish
Come play board games, card games, video games, or just chill with us and listen to music. Snacks, drink, and maybe even leftover cake provided!

Come to get lit lit lit :-)))) We will have yummy pizza, a hot dance floor, and an amazing time waiting for ya
Stresed out already? Come to pet some cute animals and eat from some A++ food carts! We'll also have dorm tours running is ya want to get an inside look of Baker.
Come by anytime to relax and grab free smoothie & snack! (‚âß‚óâ‚ó°‚óâ‚â¶)

Pizza just doesn't get any better than when you make it yourself! Come choose from a truly ludicrous number of toppings and try your hand at tossing pizza dough. Pineapple pizza, pickle pizza, pesto pizza, pizza for dessert?!?  Vegan and gluten-free options available.
Did your babtsya or vecmƒÅmi≈Üa never teach you how to make pierogies? Don't worry! We'll be your local grandmothers and show you the way :)
ever wanted to play dungeons & dragons? do you already? amazing. chat with us as you are taken through the mechanics of creating a dnd character. we'll help you come up with ideas!
Test your spice tolerance by building your own bowl of spicy ramen! Variety of hot sauce and ramens provided.
okay, it's not actually mandatory but what really is? come do art with us! it doesn't matter if you think you're any good! art isn't about being good anyway :)
Close your eyes. Press on my hands. Sleep! Come learn 'science' MIT won't teach you -- with practical demonstrations!
Come play your choice of board game from our randomly selected pool of games

Come explore the world of mathematical crochet, and help make a Hilbert curve quilt! Never touched a crochet hook? No problem. Never touched a Hilbert curve? Now's your chance! There will be plenty of yarn, a small quantity of math, and lots of good conversation.

Fish shaped waffles... Fish shaped cupcakes... Fish shaped whatever you can dream. Come join us as we explore the limits of what can be cooked in a fish shaped waffle iron. Cupcakes? Marshmallows? Fruit? Ice cream? Come find out.

An introduction to the art of tying up pretty people with pretty knots in practical and ornamental ways! WARNING: This event can expose you to adult-themed conversations, which are known to the State of California to cause discomfort in select individuals.

Let us forge a hoard of mighty weapons to defend our honor and the honor of our livestock! Come forth ye brave hero and make a foam sword. Henceforth thou shalt smack thine enemies with glorious purpose!
Boba is always best when you build it yourself. Discover your favorite boba/topping combinations today at the BMF Boba Lab.
Come listen to the stories and wonders of MIT's only laundry server of Random Hall. Stick to the end to have a chance to give our machines brand new names!

We are a sophisticated service Management education corporation teaching the art form of Lindt LINDOR truffle Chocolate Service. In our 1 hour speed butlering academy, you will understand chocolate pairing and service, interacting with your clientele, and earn a certificate of butlerology.
Enjoy the height of musical theater, eat snacks, and get ready for several hours of wacky adventures!
Collaborative city building through a map labelling tabletop RPG. Come join us!
Did you know that Random Hall has ceiling murals? I wonder how they got up there hmmm... Come decorate your future living spaces by painting the walls!
Come for the tea and bracelets, stay for the friendship! We have a cozy kitchen, everything you need to make your own tea blends, and way too much embroidery floss.
Come to Random to be served delicious food by maids with cat ears! kawaii neko maid cafe (=^-.-^=)/ nyaa~
Climb, watch climbing movies, eat some food
It's been a long day.  Come lie down, relax, and watch the sky.
Celebrate the last afternoon of REX with a plate of crepes and some classic cartoons!
there is nothing like determining your own d&d stats (via a series of challenges) to inspire self-reflection. fifth edition, of course. we're not animals.
FEED AND PET THE DESTINY DOG IMPA
Do you enjoy crochet or want to learn this delightful fiber art? Come make Cool Wiggly Shapes!
i like trains. and maps! do you? come chat with me about them while we collage cut up maps onto a wall

Are you ready for your presentation? What do you mean "what presentation"? Yes, right now! What, you've never seen these slides before? No problem! Powerpoint Karaoke: we've got random slides you've never seen before, and it's your turn to present!
Don't own anything rainbow? You can fix that! Own anything not rainbow? You can fix that too! Make new rainbow items or decorate your existing belongings.
Learn to spin balls on strings and staffs around your head without hitting yourself! Come hang out on our lovely roofdeck and learn the basics of fire spinning, just without the fire.
Think you know the Harry Potter Series inside out and backwards? Test your whit and knowledge against other Harry Potter nerds while enjoying some chocolate based foods to fend of the dementors.
Compete in a trial with some of Destiny's best Family Guy death pose impersonators to see who can Family Guy death pose the longest. Participation trophies will be provided.
It's simple: at any given moment there are at least 17 wild ladders around MIT's campus. We will show you pictures of ladders and you must guess which ones have been spotted at MIT. simple.

column1: 24 hours of Nickelodeon Show video essays
column6: Remember when a long video essay was an hour? Now spend a whole day watching video essays about nickelodeon shows you might remember from your childhood
Reeallllyy cold ice cream

Takoyaki? Whatchu tako 'bout? Come learn what takoyaki is and how to make some! Or just come to eat delicious food and spectate as people furiously rotate balls of golden doughy goodness. (Vegetarian option available)

column1: Get Buried in the Largest Plushie Pit
column6: Here we try to break the Random record of number of plushies in a giant pile! We have a lot already (squishmallows are very large) but bring your own plushies if you have them so they can be part of this momentous occasion in Random history.

Have you ever wanted to watch the critically acclaimed film 50 Shades of Grey but avoided it for its crude nature? Fear not! We have tastefully curated an edited version of the film for your viewing pleasure. Afterwards, participate in a scholarly discussion about the films merits and weaknesses.
Join us as we play a variety of games in the Jackbox collection.
watch late night movies from Random's lovely roofdeck

column1: toss baby yoda up the 282 stairwell speedrun
column6: It takes ~1.4 seconds for baby yoda to fall down the entire 282 stairwell from bonfire to destiny. Can we toss him back up faster?
no, really. there are no strings on this parachute. come play games with us on the roofdeck!
Develop your culinary abilities and panic in the four-player cooperative video game Overcooked.
Come hang out and watch a queer movie with us while decorating (and eating) cookies! All identities welcome :)
Do you have an extensive vocabulary you can't wait to share? Or do you simply love learning new words? Come join us as we play various word games that test your vocab and word association skills!

Make that cuddly Eldritch Horror friend you've always wanted! Rend some plushies asunder and reform them in your own image! A dog head here, some bat wings there, a lizard tail to pull the whole thing together and ta da! Perfection.

You are a dinousaur, a ferocious, crispy, powerful dino nugget. You're on a mission to take over the prehistoric world, but that won't come without friendship, betrayal, monching, and ponching. Join us for a yummy dino nug roleplaying game, and play ouut your nuggiest power fantasy. *Dino emoji*

You know what's even better than free food? Picking locks. Fortunately, we won't make you choose between them. Come pick your way through locks and eat through bagels, or vice versa depending on the quality of your dentist.
Long ago, you watched children's television in harmony. Then everything changed when higher education attacked... Come watch ATLA and chat!

column1: Spongebob Skin Theory: The Shocking Truth
column6:
Spongebob seems like an innocent show at first, but some things just don't add up...
Here we watch how one man finally discovered the truth: the Spongebob Skin Theory.

column1: Roofdeck Mochi Donuts -- Let's talk about cooking at MIT!
column6: What's that sizzle you hear? It's a delectable, golden-brown mochii donut deep-frying in canola oil, ready to be slathered with glaze and topped with chocolate spinkles. The surface of the donut crackles as your teeth diig into the chewy mochi center, the texture mingling with flavors of matcha and black sesame. Mouth watering yet?
Oh, your poor little meowmeow, how misunderstood... wait, who's this again? Defend your problematic fave, PowerPoint roulette version.

From Peter Parker to Jonathan Harker, nerds love a lot of things, but there's one thing they love above all else and that is correcting people. Welcome to Um, Actually! Your host will present incorrect statements about the media you know and love. It's your job to correct them.
Resolve your impostor syndrome by finding the impostor upperclassmen in a group of freshmen!

Letter writing game that's actually just analog stardew valley? Radical cat girl anarchy? If any of these sound interesting to you come try out some table top roleplaying games that we've decided have weird or unconventional premises and/or systems
Do you like to play chess? Are you hungry? Come play the classic 2v2 chess variant (bughouse) and enjoy food in mugs!

Have you ever heard of the hit game League of Legends? Or do you despise it with every atom of your being? Become a character from your favorite game in spirit and associate with like-minded leaguers or become a warrior to defeat those little league players - the choice is yours. Let's light it up!
Nobody wants to learn about MIT from MIT students. MIT AU fanfics are the best way to learn about MIT. (Accuracy not guaranteed.)

we have a funky little espresso machine and spend far too much money on our fast brain juice. come grind coffee beans with us and spend some quality time sipping coffee and chatting about MIT with friendly upperclassmen!
Learn all the different uses of a multivitamin, and why you should eat two multitools per day!

Guess Geos with us by any means possible! Learn the try hard strats such as: staring at signs, staring at cars, starting at the sky and staring in general! But... are you playing the game, or is the game playing you?

Do you love correcting people? If not, would you like to try it anyways? Come to Random Hall to enjoy a game of trivia based around correcting facts related to science fiction and fantasy. Categories will include: Star Wars, swords, Minecraft, and magic.
our dorm is a colorful maze -- come explore it, and don't forget to look up!
do you look at a white wall and seethe inside?  come paint, doodle, write, scribble, splatter, slosh, stick, ooze, and more on the white walls of black hole. leave your mark. f*ck up black hole.

column1: Make your maker, bake your maker, meet your maker, eat your maker
column6: I've heard that religion's pretty *sweet*, but what does god look like? Come make and bake your maker by shaping a sweet, pliable dough to re-create god's likeness in the most delicious and holy form---the sugar cookie.
From the makers of "I have a bad case of diarrhea", come learn brand new english sentences and exercise along the way!

It's nice to *meat* you. This vegetarian wants to sink their fangs into a rich, umami piece of pure protein. It might be *meat*iculous, but you'll find yourself s*meat*ten with some plant-based protein options.
baked beans cupcakes. also chat time
